Review:

The eighth volume of music from the WWE consists of 14 songs from wrestling stars, sometimes performed in conjunction with major-league heavy rockers (Theory of a Deadman show up, for instance, on "No Chance in Hell" with Mr. McMahon, and Saliva and Shinedown&#039;s Brent Smith team up on "Don&#039;t Question My Heart"). Basically, this is the kind of disc that you&#039;re either into or you&#039;re not; no amount of sweet-talking will make this appealing to somebody outside its intended audience. For those who do roll this way, this isn&#039;t addictive but it&#039;s a reasonably satisfying dose of testosterone. [This edition features three bonus tracks.]
